# detect XML
*.xml linguist-detectable

# detect plaintext
*.txt linguist-detectable

# detect CSV
*.csv linguist-detectable

# detect MD
*.md linguist-detectable

# Binary assets: never apply end-of-line conversion. Without this, git's
# text/binary auto-detection samples only the first 8000 bytes for a NUL byte;
# a PDF whose opening objects run longer than that (e.g. all_tcn_figures.pdf,
# first NUL at byte 10439) is misclassified as text and corrupted by
# core.autocrlf on Windows checkout — Acrobat then reports "not a valid PDF".
*.pdf   binary
*.png   binary
*.jpg   binary
*.jpeg  binary
*.gif   binary
*.ico   binary
*.ttf   binary
*.otf   binary
*.woff  binary
*.woff2 binary
*.xlsx  binary
*.xls   binary
*.docx  binary
*.pptx  binary
